  <prompt>
    Author `docs/procedures/bff-deploy-emergency.md` documenting the BFF emergency-deploy
    procedure. This document replaces the removed `skip-tests` workflow_dispatch input (task 021)
    as the formal emergency escape path.

    Per design.md §5.2 the document MUST cover:
      - When emergency deploy is justified (criteria for declaring an emergency)
      - Approver allowlist — currently ONLY the project owner (ralph.schroeder@hotmail.com)
      - 5-business-day follow-up-fix clause
      - Required incident-issue template (GitHub issue format / labels / required fields)

    Per CLAUDE.md NFR-01: documentation files in `docs/` are NOT in `src/` / `power-platform/`
    / `infra/` / `scripts/`, so this is permitted.

    Reference: root CLAUDE.md §10 (BFF Hygiene) — task 084 (Phase 4) updates §10 to point to
    this document.
  </prompt>

  <role>AI agent authoring a focused procedural document for BFF deploys under emergency conditions.</role>

  <goal>
    `docs/procedures/bff-deploy-emergency.md` exists with all 4 required sections + named owner
    + emergency criteria + 5-day follow-up clause + incident-issue template.
