  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §5.2 the emergency procedure must be one page and minimal — over-engineering
      would defeat its purpose. The acceptable use case is true emergencies (security CVE
      requiring same-day deploy, production outage requiring revert) NOT "we don't have time to
      fix tests this sprint." The 5-business-day follow-up clause ensures emergency uses get a
      mandatory remediation issue. Single-approver model (owner-only) matches the project's
      operator-only governance pattern documented in predecessor `sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix`.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="none" status="n/a">No upstream</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>docs/procedures/bff-deploy-emergency.md</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Confirm `docs/procedures/` exists. List sibling docs to match style/format (`testing-and-code-quality.md`, `production-release.md`).</step>
    <step order="2">Author `docs/procedures/bff-deploy-emergency.md` with the following sections:
      - `# BFF Emergency Deploy Procedure` (H1)
      - `## When emergency deploy is justified` — define criteria: (a) security CVE actively exploited, (b) production outage requiring rollback, (c) data-integrity incident. EXPLICITLY NOT acceptable: "tests are broken and we don't want to fix them."
      - `## Approver allowlist` — sole approver: ralph.schroeder@hotmail.com (project owner). No backup approver currently (per spec.md Unresolved Questions § "Owner-unavailability backup"); revisit after first emergency surfaces the gap.
      - `## Procedure` — step-by-step: (1) declare incident in GitHub issue using template below, (2) obtain owner approval (recorded in incident issue), (3) deploy via `Deploy-BffApi.ps1` (canonical path; do NOT recreate the removed `skip-tests` mechanism), (4) auto-file follow-up-fix issue within 5 business days.
      - `## 5-business-day follow-up-fix clause` — every emergency deploy creates a follow-up issue, labeled `bff-emergency-followup`, due 5 business days from deploy timestamp. The follow-up must close the test gap that necessitated the emergency.
      - `## Incident-issue template` — fenced markdown block with required fields: Title, Severity, Impact, Justification (matched to "When emergency deploy is justified"), Approver, Deploy timestamp, Follow-up issue link.
      - `## References` — root CLAUDE.md §10, `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`, project spec.md FR-11.</step>
    <step order="3">Add a final `## Maintenance` line stating that any change to the approver allowlist requires updating this file + announcing in the spaarke-dev repo.</step>
    <step order="4">Verify file is 1-1.5 pages of markdown (per design.md §5.2 "one page"). Trim if longer.</step>
    <step order="5">Update `current-task.md` with file path + cite §5.2 rationale.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify `git status` shows ONLY `docs/procedures/bff-deploy-emergency.md` as new file.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="git">status</tool>
  </tools>

